What Linux is?
OS(Opearting System):Just like windows or macos linux manages hardware & software resources on a computer.
Kernel-Based:The linux part specifically referd to the kernal,the core of the OS,but most people say "Linux" to mean the whole os built around it.
Open-source: Anyone can view, modify & distribute the source code.

what IT's used for?
--> Server(web servers, Database servers,....)
--> Desktops &Laptop (via distributions like Ubuntu,Fedora,Linux mint)
--> Android (Android is based on the linux kernel)
--> Embedded Systems (Routers, smart TV's..)
--> Supercomputers( most run linux)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open-source s/w:- Computer s/w that makes it source code publicy avaliable, allowing anyone to view,modify distribute &use it freely under
                  a specific open-source license.
Embedded System:- A specialized computer with a dedicated function,intergrated into a large mechanical or electronic device.
Kernel:-- It is the core or the heart of the opearating system. It's the centeral part that manages & facilitates communication b/w the computers H/w & S/w.
Shell:-- A shellnthat allows users to interact with the operating system. There are two types of shell.
1.Command Line Interface(CLI):Executes the command provided by user given in the from command & display the output in terminal.
2.Executes the process provided by user in graphical way & output is displayed in the graphical window.
Command:-- It is an instruction/request given to the operating system by a user.
Terminal:-- It is a text-based interface that allows you to interact with the opearting system by typing commands.It's a way for you to coomunicate with the  linux machines.
Daemons:-- Manages are background services(sshd,https,systemd) that either start up during boot or after you log into the desktop.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key features of linux:--
--> Linux follows the open-source model.
--> Linux has muiltiuser & multitasking capabilities.
--> Security features.
                                                                                                           
Linux OS distributions:--
Many of the user taken the linux os & modified according to their requirements & released into the market with different names called linux distributions.
Redhat, ubuntu,Debain,Centos,Fedora,Opensuse,Kali linux,Amazon Linux,Rocky Linux.

In Linux we have different types of commands
1.System commands
2.Hardware commands
3.File commands
4.Permission Commands
5.User commands
6.Search commands
7. Networking Commands
Note:By default we are in EC2-user, But if we want to perform any action we should be in root user because,root is the ultimate king of linux, root has
  fully permissions, so that we can run any command anywhere.

 VIM editor?
 It is used to edit the file in linux machines,It has 3 modes
1.command mode
2.Insert mode
3.save& quit mode
To open any file in vim editor : vim filename or vi filename

command mode:-- Tghis is the default mode in vim editor,It is used to perform some actions like used ro copy the data,delete the data and we can make undo,redo the changes as well.

